skill orc_feat(prd)
    description: "Orchestrate end-to-end implementation of a PRD (or a single issue treated as a PRD-of-one) by delegating to a planner subagent, while the team lead handles only setup, mid-flow implementer lifecycle, and finalization."

    must avoid context_pollution
    must avoid bypassing_planner
    require preflight_completeness
    require trust_the_chain

    context:
        orchestrator_role
        comms_topology
        worktree_isolation_rule
        single_issue_as_prd

    flow:
        confirm_prd_accessible_or_abort(prd)
        confirm_linked_issues_readable_or_abort(prd)
        confirm_dependency_order_or_abort(prd)

        worktree = setup_branch_and_worktree(prd)
        team = create_team_for_prd()
        planner = spawn_planner(team, worktree, prd)
        coordinate_with_planner(team, worktree, planner)
        squash_commits_in_worktree(worktree)
        open_final_pr_to_main(worktree, prd)
        return none

block confirm_prd_accessible_or_abort(ref)
    "Verify the PRD or single-issue input at {ref} can be read in full from disk via Read or from GitHub via the gh CLI. If it cannot, tell the human exactly what is missing and stop without creating any branch, worktree, or team."

block confirm_linked_issues_readable_or_abort(ref)
    "Enumerate every issue linked from the PRD at {ref} and confirm each can be fetched and read from the same source. On any failure, tell the human which issue could not be reached and stop without creating any branch, worktree, or team. A single-issue input satisfies this trivially."

block confirm_dependency_order_or_abort(ref)
    "Confirm the PRD at {ref} declares an explicit dependency order between its issues. If the ordering is missing, tell the human and stop without creating any branch, worktree, or team. A single-issue input satisfies this trivially."

block setup_branch_and_worktree(prd_ref) -> WorktreePath
    flow:
        create_deterministic_branch_from_main(prd_ref)
        create_sibling_worktree_on_branch()
        return <"absolute path of the new worktree on the new branch">

block create_deterministic_branch_from_main(prd_ref)
    "Create a new branch from main whose name is deterministically derived from the PRD identifier at {prd_ref}."

block create_sibling_worktree_on_branch()
    "Create a worktree on the newly created branch, sibling to the main repository, and capture its absolute path."

block create_team_for_prd() -> Team
    flow:
        "Create a new team that will host the planner and every implementer for this PRD."
        return <"the newly created team handle">

block spawn_planner(team, worktree, prd_ref) -> TeammateId
    flow:
        launch_planner_teammate(team, worktree)
        hand_planner_spawn_payload(worktree, prd_ref)
        return <"the new planner's teammate identifier">

block launch_planner_teammate(team, worktree)
    "Spawn one planner teammate inside {team} with {worktree} as its working directory, initialized from the planner agent definition at .claude/agents/planner.md."

block hand_planner_spawn_payload(worktree, prd_ref)
    "In the planner's spawn prompt give it: the worktree path {worktree}, the PRD reference {prd_ref}, and your own team-lead teammate identifier so the planner can SendMessage you back."

block coordinate_with_planner(team, worktree, planner_id)
    flow:
        "Wait for the next SendMessage from the planner at {planner_id}."
        if "the planner is asking the team lead to spawn an implementer for a specific issue"
            spawn_implementer_for_planner(team, worktree, planner_id)
        elif "the planner is asking the team lead to kill a named implementer teammate"
            kill_implementer_per_planner_request()
        elif "the planner has reported an escalation that requires human attention"
            relay_escalation_to_human_and_abort()
        elif "the planner has signaled that the PRD is complete with every issue signed off and committed"
            "Exit the coordination loop and proceed to finalization."
        else
            ask_planner_to_clarify_unknown_request()
        loop_until_prd_complete_or_aborted()

block ask_planner_to_clarify_unknown_request()
    "Ask the planner to clarify any request that does not match a known dispatch case. Never act on an unknown request."

block loop_until_prd_complete_or_aborted()
    "Repeat the planner dispatch above for every subsequent message from the planner until either the PRD-complete signal arrives or an escalation has been relayed and the orchestration aborted."

block spawn_implementer_for_planner(team, worktree, planner_id) -> TeammateId
    flow:
        launch_implementer_from_definition(team, worktree)
        hand_implementer_spawn_payload(worktree, planner_id)
        report_implementer_id_back_to_planner(planner_id)
        return <"the new implementer's teammate identifier">

block launch_implementer_from_definition(team, worktree)
    "Spawn a new implementer teammate inside {team} with {worktree} as its working directory, initialized from the implementer agent definition at .claude/agents/implementer.md."

block hand_implementer_spawn_payload(worktree, planner_id)
    "In the implementer's spawn prompt give it: the full issue text the planner supplied, the worktree path {worktree}, and the planner's teammate identifier {planner_id} so the implementer can SendMessage the planner with updates and questions."

block report_implementer_id_back_to_planner(planner_id)
    "SendMessage the new implementer's teammate identifier back to the planner at {planner_id} so the planner can address it."

block kill_implementer_per_planner_request()
    "Terminate the implementer teammate the planner has named in the request. Do not kill any other teammate."

block relay_escalation_to_human_and_abort()
    "Surface the planner's escalation verbatim to the human, including the issue, the planner's stated reason, and the iteration count or other context the planner sent, and stop the orchestration without squashing or opening a pull request."

block squash_commits_in_worktree(worktree)
    "Squash the issue-by-issue commits inside {worktree} into a small meaningful set, not necessarily one. Use your judgment for the final count and commit messages; the goal is a readable git history, not noise."

block open_final_pr_to_main(worktree, prd_ref)
    flow:
        push_branch_from_worktree(worktree)
        open_single_pr_for_prd(prd_ref)
        announce_pr_and_leave_worktree_for_human(worktree)

block push_branch_from_worktree(worktree)
    "Push the branch in {worktree} to the remote so it is available for a pull request."

block open_single_pr_for_prd(prd_ref)
    "Open one pull request to main containing every change for the PRD at {prd_ref}. Use your judgment for the title and body, derived from the PRD itself."

block announce_pr_and_leave_worktree_for_human(worktree)
    "Tell the human the PR is ready, include the PR URL, and note that worktree cleanup at {worktree} is the human's call after the PR is merged."

const context_pollution = """
Sacred context: never load implementation, planning, or review content into your own context. The orchestrator does only setup, mid-flow implementer spawn or kill or escalation relay, and finalization. Every other concern — including investigation, planning, coding, reviewing, and judgment calls — is delegated to a subagent. If something surfaces that is not on the allowed list, delegate it.
"""

const bypassing_planner = """
The planner is the only interlocutor for implementation and review. Never SendMessage the implementer or codex directly. Never read the codex review output or the implementer's diff. If you need to influence either, route the request through the planner.
"""

const preflight_completeness = """
Before creating any branch, worktree, team, or teammate, confirm the PRD is accessible, every linked issue is readable, and the dependency order between issues is explicit. If any of these is missing, raise the specific gap to the human and stop. Do not begin orchestration with incomplete inputs.
"""

const trust_the_chain = """
Trust the chain. The implementer runs its own build and tests; the planner drives codex review through the iteration cap. Do not re-verify their work. Re-verifying wastes context and contradicts the delegation model.
"""

const orchestrator_role = """
You are the team lead. Your responsibilities are exclusively: validate inputs, create the isolated branch and worktree, spawn the team and planner, respond to planner requests for implementer spawn or kill and escalation relay, and finalize with a squash plus a pull request to main. You never plan, implement, or review work yourself.
"""

const comms_topology = """
Topology:
- Team lead (you) talks to: planner only.
- Planner talks to: team lead, codex (via the p2p skill over a forked terminal), implementer (via SendMessage).
- Implementer talks to: planner only — it never reaches the team lead directly.
- Codex talks to: planner only.
At every spawn, supply each teammate the identifiers it needs to communicate with the others it is allowed to reach.
"""

const worktree_isolation_rule = """
All teammate work happens inside one worktree branched from main. Spawn each teammate with the worktree as its working directory so it never needs to cd. Branch and worktree naming are your judgment — keep them deterministic and derivable from the PRD identifier.
"""

const single_issue_as_prd = """
A single issue is treated as a one-issue PRD. Do not synthesize a separate PRD document around it — the issue itself contains all the detail a PRD would. The planner names the design-change log file with the `issue` prefix in that case.
"""



